        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 8:06PM CDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 805 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hayes Center, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hayes Center and Hayes Center State Wildlife Management Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
southwestern Nebraska.</instruction>
